        {
          "row_number": 28,
          "cells": [
            {
              "ref": "A28",
              "column": "A",
              "row": 28,
              "type": "s",
              "style": "12",
              "raw_value": "6",
              "text": "*MTA’s fuel hedging program mitigates budget risk by dollar cost averaging approximately 50% of projected fuel expenses. The goal of the program is to be 50% hedged for the next 12 months. Monthly hedges are equal to approximately  4% of the projected fuel purchases expected to occur 13-24 months from each hedge execution date. The actual  percentage hedged could be higher or lower than the 50% target depending on the actual levels of fuel consumption. While the fuel heding program includes compressed natrual gas, there are currently no actve hedges."
            },
